.SS peek
.PP
Usage: \f[C]peek\ <dac|lms|si>\ <address>\ [num\ addresses]\f[]
.PP
The peek command can read any of the devices hanging off the FPGA which
includes the LMS6002D transceiver, VCTCXO trim DAC or the Si5338 clock
generator chip.
.PP
If \f[C]num_addresses\f[] is supplied, the address is incremented by 1
and another peek is performed.
.PP
Valid Address Ranges:
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]dac\f[]: 0 to 255
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]lms\f[]: 0 to 127
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]si\f[]: 0 to 255
.PP
Example:
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]peek\ si\ ...\f[]
.SS poke
.PP
Usage: \f[C]poke\ <dac|lms|si>\ <address>\ <data>\f[]
.PP
The poke command can write any of the devices hanging off the FPGA which
includes the LMS6002D transceiver, VCTCXO trim DAC or the Si5338 clock
generator chip.
.PP
If \f[C]num_addresses\f[] is supplied, the address is incremented by 1
and another poke is performed.
.PP
Valid Address Ranges:
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]dac\f[]: 0 to 255
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]lms\f[]: 0 to 127
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]si\f[]: 0 to 255
.PP
Example:
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]poke\ lms\ ...\f[]
